\section{Dataset}

\subsection{Corpus Description}
The dataset consists of doctor-patient dialogues paired with reference clinical summaries (gold summaries), stored in JSONL format. Each record encodes the original multilingual dialogue, the target language label, and the corresponding ground-truth summary authored by clinical experts. The dialogues capture realistic clinical interactions and exhibit features typical of clinical discourse: domain-specific terminology, code-switching, elliptical constructions, and turn-taking artifacts. To ensure rigorous evaluation across languages, we curated a highly verified, parallel test set comprising exactly 60 scenarios per language. 

